text: Newcastle () is a barony in County Wicklow, Republic of Ireland. ==Etymology== Newcastle barony derives its name from the village of Newcastle. ==Location== Newcastle barony is located in eastern County Wicklow, opening onto the Irish Sea. ==History== The Uí Theig (O'Tighe), cousins to the Uí Máil, are noted early here, as well as the Uí Braen Deilgni, a branch of the Uí Garrchon. This was part of O'Byrne (Ó Broin) country after the 12th century, referred to in Gaelic as Crioch Branach. ==List of settlements== Below is a list of settlements in Newcastle barony: *Ashford *Glenealy (northern part) *Kilcoole *Newcastle *Newtownmountkennedy ==References== Category:Baronies of County Wicklow
title: Newcastle (County Wicklow barony)
